reviews.review_text: Grateful Dead at their Best! Crisp soundboard.  Bob and Jerry's vocals are awesome!  Brent's keyboards stand out.  Thanks for uploading this!
Definitive Source The best source for this top 5 1982 show!

1982 Is GD’s most underrated year. They are on fire all year long, and this could be the best show of the year - one of the top few no question. It’s both confusing and disappointing that so many people overlook how great this year is.

Listening to this tonight The Seamons matrix never fails to amaze: the richness of the sound is just amazing. He adds just the proper amount of audience to where it compliments rather than distracts.
The show itself is great, lost of personal favorites there: Scarlet Fire, Terrapin, Dupree's, Stella. It is all well played too.
